# Security Policy

This document describes which versions of {{project_name.snakeCase()}} are
supported with security updates and how to report a vulnerability.

## Supported Versions

Only the latest minor release receives security updates. Older releases are not
supported.

| Version              | Supported          |
| -------------------- | ------------------ |
| Latest minor release | :white_check_mark: |
| Older releases       | :x:                |

## Reporting a Vulnerability

If you discover a security vulnerability in {{project_name.snakeCase()}},
please report it privately to the maintainers. For projects hosted on GitHub,
open a private security advisory through the repository's **Security** tab.
Otherwise, contact the maintainers directly.

Please do **not** open a public issue, pull request, or discussion for
security reports.

When reporting a vulnerability, include as much of the following information as
possible:

- A description of the issue and its potential impact.
- Steps to reproduce the issue.
- The version(s) affected.
- Any suggested fixes or mitigations, if available.

The maintainers will acknowledge your report as soon as possible and work with
you to investigate the issue and coordinate a fix and disclosure.
